<br>
Yesterday, I participated in a Hate raid. the majority members were from my guild Arcane Evol.  A guild member lead the raid, he had joined Arcane Evol about two weeks ago.  He brought along several of his RL friends to the raid but were not in our guild. <br>
<br>
Raid started out like most raids, everything seemed normal but as time progressed it became more and more apparant the raid was for raid leader and his friends only.  <br>
<br>
We were in hate for about four hours, took down p'tasa, and then maestro was pulled, monk fd, but maestro agro onto the whole grp and commenced to wipe us out. Clerics camped.<br>
<br>
ALL during the raid, Raid leader refused to let any other guild members join, even tho we stayed at entrance for an hour or two. After we get to moving inwards, he then allows more of his friends join the raid, but still refused to let any more from Arcane Evol join. In tells he would tell me, we are full. Then later on, all of a sudden we had room for his friends.<br>
<br>
He made several adjustments to his team to ensure his group recieved most of the exp. In group chat, he spoke to his RL friends asking why they were not getting exp, and they discussed it, then made changes. <br>
<br>
Well, after we got wiped out, <br>
<br>
I spoke in channel chat for the first time. I stated that we were not capable of taking down the hi level mob, and that we had been on the raid for over four hours, many wanted to split the loot and leave.  The cleric RL friend of the raid leader, immediately got very rude and beligerant with me, and told me to SHUT UP or he would not rez me. <br>
<br>
I took it to tells. In tells the raid leader ignored me. The cleric was obnoxious and rude, and again threatened me.<br>
<br>
Well, this is the first time that my corpse was held as ransom. I could not believe the shallowness of the individual to hide behind his screen and become so unruly.<br>
<br>
Immediately a guild mate rezzed me, and said he was way out of line.  I gathered our guild members, we were done with the soured raid and the majority of the raid members were gating out.  Naturally they refused to split loot and kept all the diamonds and drops. Stated raid was not over they were staying.<br>
<br>
As a guild we gated out. I then /guildremove raid leader from our guild.<br>
<br>
I have been playing EQ for a little over 2 years and never have been treated so rudely. This was the first time I ever had grouped with the rude cleric.<br>
<br>
We all develop lists of individuals who piss us off or for one reason or another and absolutely refuse to grp/help or play with them.<br>
<br>
In my two years time of playing, only one person has made &quot;my list&quot; that I will not play or help in any way.  I am laid back and can get along with just about anyone so it is hard to make my list.<br>
<br>
After last night, I decided to make some room and add a few names to my list. <br>
<br>
My corpse is of value to me, due to the time, money, energy placed into my character.  But, I will not be manipulated or controlled by a rude cleric who threatens me, that if I do not shut up, he will not rez me.  This is totally ridiculous and unacceptable behavior. I can understand if I had been rude or obnoxious but I was not. My statement in raid channel was not even directed towards the cleric. Never before had I ever spoken to him.<br>
<br>
Rant off.<br>
